  "texts": [
    "These systems often rely on the collection, processing, and interpretation of personal data, such as users' sensory preferences, dietary histories, and even physiological responses.",
    "Such data are highly sensitive and may inadvertently reveal information related to health status, lifestyle, or cultural identity.",
    "Without robust privacy protections, this information could be misused by third parties or exploited for commercial purposes beyond users' original intent.",
    "Therefore, it is essential to implement transparent data management protocols that outline clear rules for data ownership, access control, and retention.",
    "Compliance with data protection regulations, such as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), should be a baseline requirement (Hao et al. 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Compliance with data protection regulations, such as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), should be a baseline requirement (Hao et al. 2023)."
  ]
}